programme.title: SEVE - Artist, Fighter, Legend
programme.desc: Seve Ballesteros was an artist, a golfing Picasso. He was a fighter against back injury, rivals on the golf course, a disintegrating swing, and finally cancer. This is his story, from members of his inner circle, other sporting greats and from himself via newly unearthed material.

programme.title: BVB 09 Stories - Who we are: Uprooting (Episode 3)
programme.desc: After the initial games, the First Eleven is established where the next generation of footballers may end up playing a crucial role for BVB. While Giovanni Reyna has already had a breakthrough into the pro team, the even younger Youssoufa Moukoko works on his debut. How do these two exceptional teenagers cope with the challenges of being in the public eye from a young early? This episode takes a close look into the challenges of talent promotion and social responsibility.

programme.title: BVB 09 Stories - Who we are: The Greed for Success (Episode 4)
programme.desc: When Erling Haaland signed with BVB it created a huge media stir. A year on, he is due a review of his outstanding first and record-breaking year at Dortmund. However, for Haaland, there has been more to this last year than just being on the pitch, such as, how has he grown as a player and a person? How do friends, companions and his father perceive his development? Is there any unnoticed potential concerning his career? Narrated by Haaland himself along with his closest advisor, his father, Alfie, this episode is a truly personal story.

programme.title: BVB 09 Stories - Who we are: Never forget (Episode 5)
programme.desc: In January, focus is on commemorating the atrocities committed by the Nazis. BVB is doing commemorative work and wants to preserve this for future generations. The episode is set in the former Auschwitz concentration camp in present-day Poland. Holocaust survivor Eva Szepesi and others share their stories, contributing to the importance of remembering these events and emphasising the social responsibility of football.

programme.title: BVB 09 Stories - Who we are: Real Love (Episode 6)
programme.desc: “Echte liebe”. A brand claim or much more? Mats Hummels talks about the old and new times at Dortmund. Norbert Dickel meets Dede, and Jürgen Klopp remembers an almost perfect championship team. In addition, former talent Dario Scuderi tells his incredible story that will forever connect him to BVB.

programme.title: BVB 09 Stories - Who we are: Rookie review (Episode 7)
programme.desc: We return to Moukoko and Reyna´s stories and look at the development of the two talents. How´s Reyna doing? Is Moukoko scoring goals from the start of the pros? And if not, what are the consequences? This episode also introduces Jude Bellingham, who is having an impressive first season as a youngster.

programme.title: The Secrets of La Roja – World Champions 2010
programme.desc: On the 11th July 2010, Spain’s national team reached its goal of winning the World Cup, a victory that was felt by the team and nation as a whole. Despite this successful ending, “La Roja” had to overcome various struggles and difficulties in order to become legendary. The team arrived in South Africa with the triumph of the 2008 European Football Championship under their belt and Vicente del Bosque leading the way. There was a general feeling of favoritism attributed to ""La Roja"" and while the defeat against Switzerland in the first match came as a shock, it motivated Del Bosque and his team to come together and focus on one intention: good football and one goal: to make history.

programme.title: Inside Kilian Jornet
programme.desc: For Kilian Jornet, the world's greatest mountain athlete, the arrival of his thirties coincided with the best and worst year of his life. This documentary follows Jornet through an intense 10-day tour of 10 cities around the world, allowing the public to see, for the first time, everything that goes on around the professional athlete, and revealing his lesser-known, uninhibited side. Between presentations, interviews, and brand commitments, and with only a few hours' sleep, the athlete reflects on a year marked by injuries his search for the balance between competition and personal projects and the arrival of his first daughter.

programme.title: Break Point: a Davis Cup Story
programme.desc: Led by Rafa Nadal, the Spanish team were this year’s favourite until they suffered a serious setback. The team’s number two player, Roberto Bautista, had to leave the competition for his hometown to be at his father´s side during the last hours of his life. Without Bautista, Nadal and Feliciano López heroically managed to lead the team into the final. But then came the news that thrilled tennis fans worldwide: Bautista is coming back to the competition after his father´s funeral, and he´s ready to play. United again, the members of the Spanish team fight for victory in the grand final, where something far beyond tennis is at stake.

programme.title: Made in Senegal
programme.desc: Made in Senegal is a story about will, dreams, determination, faith, rebellion, courage and love. The film invites us on a journey through Sadio´s different and highly diverse worlds - from the rural life in a small village in the far south of Senegal to the spotlight of world football by playing for Liverpool FC, even winning the Champions Leagues as number 10 with the world watching… The interaction of animations, documentary scenes, a diverse set of in-depth interviews and archive footage brings Sadio´s past to life and creates an exciting and emotional plot.

Lionel Macomb has been the reigning king of conservative talk radio, delighting his fans and enraging his opponents with his angry charisma and caustic wit. He has his perfect world turned upside down when his 16-year-old niece, Tess, shows up seeking help with a family crisis. In Tess, Lionel has finally met his match: a smart, determined, brazenly honest sparring partner who forces Lionel to confront the complicated family he left behind.

programme.title: Mozart and the Whale
programme.desc: A charming and heartfelt romantic drama starring Josh Hartnett and Radha Mitchell. New York taxi driver Donald Morton has Asperger's syndrome, a type of autism. Proficient with numbers but shy around people, Donald organizes a support group for others with his condition. Isabelle Sorenson, who is direct to a fault and practical, but easily upset by any perceived insult, joins the group. The two fall in love, but their mutual difficulty in coping with their condition threatens their fragile relationship.

programme.title: Witchville
programme.desc: In the Middle Ages, Erik and Jason seek out his compatriot Malachy and force him to return to his homeland. When they arrive, they find that Malachy's father, the King, is dead and their lands are completely devastated. Both seek revenge against the Evil Red Queen.

programme.title: Eye for an Eye
programme.desc: John Travolta, Morgan Freeman, Famke Janssen, and Brendan Fraser lend their talents to this searing detective thriller. Travolta plays Carson Philips, a hard-drinking L.A. private eye, who takes a case in his old hometown of Galveston, Texas. While searching for a missing woman, Philips must confront a crime boss, a shady doctor, a sexy club singer, his former lover — and his own dark, disturbing past.

programme.title: Gutshot Straight
programme.desc: A professional poker player falls deep into the underworld when he takes an unexpected wager from a mysterious high roller. In order to protect himself and his family, he must try and get to the truth as he’s forced into a murder plot making him the prime target for revenge. This action thriller’s star cast includes George Eads (TV's CSI), AnnaLynne McCord (TV's 90210), Steven Seagal (A Good Man, Hard to Kill), Vinnie Jones (Lock, Stock and Two Smoking Barrels, Snatch), Stephen Lang (Avatar), Tia Carrere (Wayne’s World, True Lies) and Ted Levine (American Gangster, Shutter Island).

programme.title: Kill Zone 2
programme.desc: Undercover cop Kit (Wu Jing) becomes a junkie in order to catch Mr Hung (Louis Koo), the mastermind behind a crime syndicate. When the operation goes sour and Kit blows his cover, his supervisor and uncle Wah (Simon Yam) decides to terminate the operation. When Kit disappears without a trace, Wah defies the order from his commanding officer and tracks Kit to a prison in Thailand.

programme.title: Jimmy P
programme.desc: A troubled Native American veteran forms an extraordinary friendship with his maverick French psychoanalyst as they try to find a cure to his suffering.
